How to set this project up in QtCreator (2.6)
---------------------------------------------
Note: «opm-root» is placeholder for a common suite directory.

1. File | Open File or Project...
2. Browse to "CMakeLists.txt" in «opm-root»/src/opm-verteq.
   Open.
3. Build directory: «opm-root»/bld/opm-verteq
   Next.
4. Arguments: -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug -Dopm-core_DIR=«opm-root»/bld/opm-core -DPRECOMPILE_HEADERS=ON -DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS=ON
   Run CMake
   Finish
5. Projects (on the sidebar)
6. Build & Run
   Build
   Build Steps
   Details
   Targets: [X] opmverteq

7. File | Open File or Project...
8. Browse to "CMakeLists.txt" in «opm-root»/src/opm-verteq/examples/2d
   Open
9. Build directory: «opm-root»/bld/opm-verteq/examples/2d
   Next.
10. Arguments: -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug -Dopm-core_DIR=«opm-root»/bld/opm-core -Dopm-verteq_DIR=-Dopm-core_DIR=«opm-root»/bld/opm-verteq
    Run CMake
	Finish
11. Projects (on the sidebar)
12. co2_2d:
    Build & Run
	Build
	Build Steps
	Details
	Targets: [X] co2_2d
13. Run (sibling to Build)
    Run configuration: co2_2d
	Arguments: tube.param
	Working directory: «opm-root»/bld/opm-verteq/examples/2d/bin
14. Dependencies (sibling to Build & Run)
15. [X] opm-verteq

If you want to use another compiler, you can set it like this:

16. Build & Run
    Build
	Build Environment
	Add
	Variable: CC      Value: gcc-4.8
	Variable: CXX     Value: g++-4.8
17. rm «opm-root»/bld/opm-verteq/CMakeCache.txt
18. CMake
    Reconfigure project: Run cmake

This procedure must be repeated in *both* projects.

19. Build | Build All
